# What Wallet Applications/Extensions Work with Bittensor?

In addition to the Chrome extension https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/bittensor-wallet/bdgmdoedahdcjmpmifafdhnffjinddgc and the iPhone mobile app at  https://apps.apple.com/pl/app/bittensor-wallet/id6476235156 (from the Opentensor team), there are several other options. Note that the iOS application **still has not been approved by Apple and so does not currently support the dynamic TAO upgrade**.

First, there's https://tensorwallet.ca/ \*, by our very own Vune. In addition, most Polkadot ecosystem hot wallets work with TAO, including the powerful but complex polkadot.js\* (https://polkadot.js.org/), Talisman\* (https://www.talisman.xyz/), SubWallet (https://www.subwallet.app/), and Nova Wallet (https://novawallet.io/). And if you are very security-oriented, there's the air-gapped Polkadot Vault (https://signer.parity.io/#about), which you can run on an old Android phone or iPhone as a cold wallet, as well as Tangem (https://tangem.com/), another cold wallet option. 

\* Should work with the dTAO upgrade; options *not* marked with an asterisk haven't been confirmed yet.

Since your tokens exist on-chain and wallets are just interfaces to interact with them (using your seed phrase is allows the wallet interface to generate the public/private keypair that will allow it to authenticate transactions for you on the blockchain), feel free to try a few and see what you like best!

Remember to be very careful with your sensitive account information!  **Only people who want to hijack your account will tell you that they need your seed/mnemonic phrase** and be especially careful about fake "Bittensor Wallet" websites, which are designed to steal it.
